00:07:06.859 --> 00:07:08.527
SCHILLINGER:
People with diabetes,

00:07:08.560 --> 00:07:10.229
because they've got
a lot of sugar on their skin,

00:07:10.262 --> 00:07:11.831
the fungus loves
to hang out there--

00:07:11.864 --> 00:07:14.133
it's moist, it's warm,
it's sweet--

00:07:14.166 --> 00:07:17.603
and they grow foot fungus,
athlete's foot,

00:07:17.636 --> 00:07:18.838
but in a person with diabetes,

00:07:18.871 --> 00:07:20.639
it can be the portal
to death, right?

00:07:20.672 --> 00:07:23.642
So, the athlete's foot begins
to burrow in the skin

00:07:23.675 --> 00:07:25.077
and create cracks in the skin,

00:07:25.110 --> 00:07:27.012
and that's, like,
the perfect opportunity

00:07:27.045 --> 00:07:30.082
for more virulent bacteria,
dangerous bacteria,

00:07:30.115 --> 00:07:32.084
to enter into the skin

00:07:32.117 --> 00:07:37.656
and begin to infiltrate
the entirety of the foot.

00:07:37.689 --> 00:07:39.225
Okay, I think
you got to start...

00:07:39.258 --> 00:07:41.160
