00:33:39.616 --> 00:33:41.285
DAN LIEBERMAN:
The average American eats

00:33:41.318 --> 00:33:42.887
about 100 pounds
of sugar a year,

00:33:42.920 --> 00:33:45.022
which means
that there are Americans

00:33:45.055 --> 00:33:48.392
who actually eat more than
100 pounds of sugar a year.

00:33:48.425 --> 00:33:49.827
We started off
as hunter-gatherers,

00:33:49.860 --> 00:33:51.362
which we were
for millions of years.

00:33:51.395 --> 00:33:54.799 line:0%
A hunter-gatherer,
if he or she is lucky,

00:33:54.832 --> 00:33:56.534 line:0%
gets about ten pounds
of sugar a year.

00:33:56.567 --> 00:34:01.005
So, we have an order
of magnitude increase

00:34:01.038 --> 00:34:03.374 line:0%
in the amount of sugar
that's available to us.

00:34:03.407 --> 00:34:07.711 line:0%
And we simply never evolved
to handle that much sugar.

00:34:07.744 --> 00:34:09.713
A common phrase
is that genes load the gun

00:34:09.746 --> 00:34:11.082
and environment
pulls the trigger.

00:34:11.115 --> 00:34:14.051
Genes we inherit,
and they change very slowly.

00:34:14.084 --> 00:34:16.087
But environments can change
really fast.

00:34:16.120 --> 00:34:18.656
And what's happened is that
we still have the same genes

00:34:18.689 --> 00:34:21.392
as our great-grandparents or
our great-great-grandparents.

00:34:21.425 --> 00:34:24.395
But the environments in which
we live have shifted rapidly,

00:34:24.428 --> 00:34:26.831
and our bodies
are poorly adapted

00:34:26.864 --> 00:34:28.432
to those modern environments.

00:34:28.465 --> 00:34:33.671
And as a result, we're
much more likely to get sick.

00:34:33.704 --> 00:34:35.873
♪ ♪

00:34:35.906 --> 00:34:38.375
NARRATOR:
