glucose monitor,

01:25:59.920 --> 01:26:02.790
which measures blood sugar
every five minutes

01:26:02.823 --> 01:26:05.326
and transmits the information.

01:26:05.359 --> 01:26:08.095 line:0%
As it was on my body,
flush with my body,

01:26:08.128 --> 01:26:10.998 line:0%
I would press this button,
and it would go, "Bink."

01:26:11.031 --> 01:26:13.000 line:0%
And then I would go like that,

01:26:13.033 --> 01:26:16.037 line:0%
and then it would be on me.

01:26:16.070 --> 01:26:19.073
And I can take my phone

01:26:19.106 --> 01:26:22.243
and check
what my blood sugar level is.

01:26:22.276 --> 01:26:23.244
Let's see.

01:26:23.277 --> 01:26:24.245
Let's take a look.

01:26:24.278 --> 01:26:26.080
Ah, it's 101.

01:26:26.113 --> 01:26:28.216
It's perfect.

01:26:28.249 --> 01:26:33.721
But this would have been
a crazy fantasy

01:26:33.754 --> 01:26:35.089
even ten years ago.

01:26:35.122 --> 01:26:36.624
There was no such thing.

01:26:36.657 --> 01:26:38.859
My continuous glucose monitor

01:26:38.892 --> 01:26:43.564
is by far my favorite way
to manage my diabetes,

01:26:43.597 --> 01:26:45.967
and it's what makes me
feel the safest.

01:26:46.000 --> 01:26:49.604
And then my mom is also on
what they call the share app,

01:26:49.637 --> 01:26:52.506
and so she is able
to get my blood sugars, too.

01:26:52.539 --> 01:26:55.209
So, if I went dangerously...
dangerously low,

01:26:55.242 --> 01:26:57.311
and I passed out in the kitchen,

01:26:57.344 --> 01:27:00.081
and she got an alert,
