looks like in our community.

01:50:44.403 --> 01:50:46.239
So, thank you.

01:50:46.272 --> 01:50:50.410
"My mother's strict hand kept
soda cans out of our fridge,

01:50:50.443 --> 01:50:54.714
"knowing what a fountain
of sugar can do to our insides.

01:50:54.747 --> 01:50:58.017
"Thank God for her intuition
and deep distrust

01:50:58.050 --> 01:51:00.086
for what this nation
paints pretty."

01:51:00.119 --> 01:51:02.155
WALLS: "But there always
has been,

01:51:02.188 --> 01:51:05.525
"and forever will be,
a family cookout

01:51:05.558 --> 01:51:08.027
"on the first Saturday in August
every year.

01:51:08.060 --> 01:51:10.063
"As for the menu--

01:51:10.096 --> 01:51:12.765
"fish filets and chicken parts
battered just bright enough

01:51:12.798 --> 01:51:15.101
"to reflect the sun's
gracious glow,

01:51:15.134 --> 01:51:17.270
"the plumpest pecan pork chops

01:51:17.303 --> 01:51:19.472
"smothered in gravy more tender
than a grateful patch

01:51:19.505 --> 01:51:21.708
of farmland
swallowed by rainfall..."

01:51:21.741 --> 01:51:25.011
HURLEY:
We're living in a world

01:51:25.044 --> 01:51:28.715
that is perfect
for making diabetes flourish.

01:51:28.748 --> 01:51:29.716
WALLS:
"Corn bread,

01:51:29.749 --> 01:51:31.451
"soft like a crumbly pastry,

01:51:31.484 --> 01:51:33.519
like, too good
not to be dessert."

01:51:33.552 --> 01:51:36.456
To really change things,

01:51:36.489 --> 01:51:41.094
we need to start remaking
the environment

01:51:41.127 --> 01:51:43.096
in which we live.

01:51:43.129 --> 01:51:45.098
CARVAJAL: Hi, my name is
Gretchen Carvajal.

01:51:45.131 --> 01:51:46.632
I'm a Youth Speaks alum.

01:51:46.665 --> 01:51:48.601
I'm now poet mentor
for the organization.

01:51:48.634 --> 01:51:49.902
And so, just, yeah,

01:51:49.935 --> 01:51:52.238
I just feel real blessed
to be in the building.

01:51:52.271 --> 01:51:55.308
"I want to be able to eat
without second-guessing,

01:51:55.341 --> 01:51:58.077
"without thinking about
a smaller version of myself,

01:51:58.110 --> 01:52:02.315
without thinking about food
as a weapon or a setback."

01:52:02.348 --> 01:52:04.784
♪ ♪

01:52:04.817 --> 01:52:07.920
LEE: As of now, the way I feel,
I feel great.

01:52:07.953 --> 01:52:10.757
I got my shoes on,
I got the inserts in there,

01:52:10.790 --> 01:52:12.859
and you'll see me,
I'm in the gym

01:52:12.892 --> 01:52:15.661
trying to run around
a little bit,

01:52:15.694 --> 01:52:17.196
and I'm just, I'm just thankful

01:52:17.229 --> 01:52:19.499
that I was able to have
a successful surgery

01:52:19.532 --> 01:52:22.502
and be able to move forward
afterwards.

01:52:22.535 --> 01:52:24.170
SCHILLINGER: I think we learned
with Monteil

01:52:24.203 --> 01:52:27.006
that social factors
are the main driver

01:52:27.039 --> 01:52:29.742
of who gets diabetes,

01:52:29.775 --> 01:52:32.178
who suffers the complications
from them,

01:52:32.211 --> 01:52:34.514
and why so many people
are disabled from it,

01:52:34.547 --> 01:52:37.884
particularly in
vulnerable communities.

01:52:37.917 --> 01:52:41.420
And that needs to change.

01:52:41.453 --> 01:52:43.489
CARVAJAL:
"My mother's side has diabetes.

01:52:43.522 --> 01:52:45.424
"Diabetes is more and more
a curse

01:52:45.457 --> 01:52:47.593
"that we thought
we brought to ourselves.

01:52:47.626 --> 01:52:51.764
"We try to break it with a
spell, a potion, and a ritual.

01:52:51.797 --> 01:52:53.432
"What is insulin, but a potion?

01:52:53.465 --> 01:52:55.835
"What is a spell,
but a diagnosis?

01:52:55.868 --> 01:52:58.204
"We take a tiny needle
and prick our finger.

01:52:58.237 --> 01:53:00.139
What is a blood sacrifice
to a blood test?"

01:53:00.172 --> 01:53:03.509
CLOSE: Maybe the next step
is a movement,

01:53:03.542 --> 01:53:06.045
a shared war on diabetes fought
by type 1s, type 2s,

01:53:06.078 --> 01:53:11.684
families, communities,
everyone, everywhere.

01:53:11.717 --> 01:53:13.786
In order to win the war
on diabetes,

01:53:13.819 --> 01:53:15.454
everyone has to be in.

01:53:15.487 --> 01:53:19.091
♪ ♪

01:53:19.124 --> 01:53:21.194
WASHINGTON:
You got one life to live.

01:53:21.227 --> 01:53:23.062
Make it your best.

01:53:23.095 --> 01:53:24.230
Eat healthy.

01:53:24.263 --> 01:53:27.700
In the end, diabetes can be

01:53:27.733 --> 01:53:30.503
a thing of the past.

01:53:32.171 --> 01:53:35.208
CARVAJAL: "Give a droplet of
yourself every night and see.

01:53:35.241 --> 01:53:37.610
"One day,
the sugar won't be as sweet.

01:53:37.643 --> 01:53:41.247
"But the food isn't
what cursed us, I promise.

01:53:41.280 --> 01:53:42.682
"It's what nourished.

01:53:42.715 --> 01:53:45.218
It's what kept
our stories true."

